Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:07.90,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1879\N(What is now) Menlo Park, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:09.19,Main,,0,0,0,,What's happening?\N"The Year 1879\N(What is now) Menlo Park, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.19,0:00:09.32,Main,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.32,0:00:11.78,Main,,0,0,0,,The weather was so nice earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:13.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Focus already!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.07,0:00:14.91,Main,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.91,0:00:18.24,Main,,0,0,0,,A thread of cotton treated\Nwith soot for a filament.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.24,0:00:19.54,Main,,0,0,0,,It'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:23.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir, it came from the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.79,0:00:26.79,Main,,0,0,0,,What are those idiots doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.88,0:00:37.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Can it be... This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.07,0:02:19.82,Main,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:19.95,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.95,0:02:20.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 12\NCherished Scientists"\NI don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.16,Main,,0,0,0,,But it could be a fissure in space-time!\N"Episode 12\NCherished Scientists"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:24.45,Main,,0,0,0,,But it could be a fissure in space-time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.45,0:02:27.00,Main,,0,0,0,,A-- A fissure in space-time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.34,0:02:44.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, grab on to the ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:49.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:52.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine! You stay still!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:53.81,Main,,0,0,0,,But Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:02:56.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:58.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:02:59.65,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.65,0:03:02.57,Main,,0,0,0,,It could be a time paradox variation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:04.03,Main,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.91,0:03:07.79,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:13.04,Main,,0,0,0,,It's when something causes\Na disturbance in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:15.79,Main,,0,0,0,,What kind of thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:17.92,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:19.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.17,0:03:20.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:35.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It's no use. I can't control it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:37.32,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't bring them back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:39.65,Main,,0,0,0,,What if they're dragged into that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.74,0:03:44.28,Main,,0,0,0,,They could be thrown to\Nthe far edge of space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:47.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:54.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:01.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Can you hear me, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:02.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.84,0:04:05.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Use the compass to get back here right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.64,0:04:10.72,Main,,0,0,0,,There's an abnormality in the system.\NWe can't bring you back from our end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:13.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that Shun? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.10,0:04:15.35,Main,,0,0,0,,The TSS is out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.61,0:04:23.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:27.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Is there a way to get back using this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.41,0:04:29.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:32.33,Main,,0,0,0,,How can we get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:33.71,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.71,0:04:37.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course! This is the cause!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.25,0:04:38.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:42.46,Main,,0,0,0,,You said the third armillary compass\Nwas on the floor of the laboratory?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:43.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:46.72,Main,,0,0,0,,There were only two armillary\Ncompasses at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:49.76,Main,,0,0,0,,You have one. And the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.76,0:04:51.72,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.72,0:04:54.64,Main,,0,0,0,,These two armillary compasses are the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:55.94,Main,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:59.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Two copies of the same thing can't exist\Nin the same place at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:01.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:03.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut off the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:04.24,Main,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:07.95,Main,,0,0,0,,If I did that, they'd be lost forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:09.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Just shut off the power for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:13.45,Main,,0,0,0,,We'll fix that and then restart the program!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.45,0:05:16.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Restart it? How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:20.67,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no guarantee that we'll be\Nable to do that without a compass!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:24.92,Main,,0,0,0,,The system's going to catch fire!\NYou just want to let that happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.92,0:05:25.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.88,0:05:27.72,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:28.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:29.35,Main,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:32.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Eiji! Come back quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.73,0:05:39.23,Main,,0,0,0,,You said this is the cause since two\Nof it exist in the same place and time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:43.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll return it to the 21st century.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:47.65,Main,,0,0,0,,At this rate, you, I, and\Nyour daughter will all die!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:50.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Head back before me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:53.45,Main,,0,0,0,,What about you? I won't go without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.37,0:05:56.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:05:58.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:00.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:02.00,Main,,0,0,0,,You won't do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:06.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:08.88,Main,,0,0,0,,How do I get back to the 21st century?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:11.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, don't tell him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:13.64,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:16.60,Main,,0,0,0,,--In that case...\N--Mikage... damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.60,0:06:20.56,Main,,0,0,0,,The dial! Turn the dial on\Nthe bottom of the compass!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:21.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:23.65,Main,,0,0,0,,The dial?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:26.03,Main,,0,0,0,,That's how you get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:43.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing's happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:45.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:48.34,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:53.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, what's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:57.31,Main,,0,0,0,,The link's been severed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.31,0:07:00.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I warned you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:02.06,Main,,0,0,0,,You mean it's broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:05.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Then... Mari and Eiji are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:07.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:09.24,Main,,0,0,0,,They can't come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.24,0:07:11.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:13.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:17.29,Main,,0,0,0,,It's no use! I'm going to be sucked in!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:19.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:23.92,Main,,0,0,0,,You said the problem was having\Ntwo of these in one place?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:24.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.92,0:07:27.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Then if one of them disappears...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:29.21,Main,,0,0,0,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.39,0:07:35.14,Main,,0,0,0,,L-Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.98,0:07:43.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:07:58.74,Main,,0,0,0,,What curious weather...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:00.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you to focus!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.62,0:08:02.08,Main,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.42,0:08:07.34,Main,,0,0,0,,It died down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.55,0:08:10.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:11.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.55,0:08:13.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:15.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:24.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that how the armillary compass\Nended up on the floor in the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:28.90,Main,,0,0,0,,The compass that got sucked in\Ngot sent to the floor of the basement?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.90,0:08:30.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:32.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:34.24,Main,,0,0,0,,--Eiji?\N--What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:39.79,Main,,0,0,0,,The system re-established\Nthe link automatically!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:52.51,Main,,0,0,0,,An overload!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:54.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you to shut off the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:57.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:00.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Idiot! We'll burn to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.14,0:09:04.02,Main,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous!\NBurn to death here if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:05.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:10.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Ms. Kuroki, let's run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.32,0:09:12.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't abandon Mr. Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.57,0:09:14.03,Main,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:20.41,Main,,0,0,0,,H-Hey! You two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:21.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.58,0:09:24.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun, Waka, you run, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:25.96,Main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:27.42,Main,,0,0,0,,You've done enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:30.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Untie us already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:31.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Can you stand, Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.84,0:09:33.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.46,0:09:35.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Hand it over...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:37.84,Main,,0,0,0,,The compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.84,0:09:39.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Hand it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:42.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Turning the dial won't get you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.93,0:09:44.73,Main,,0,0,0,,We don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.73,0:09:47.31,Main,,0,0,0,,If they do regain control of the system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:49.65,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll need a compass to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.65,0:09:51.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:55.78,Main,,0,0,0,,A man like you wouldn't\Nuse it for anything good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.78,0:09:58.86,Main,,0,0,0,,What would you use it for, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:10:02.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Taking an educational trip\Nthrough the history of science?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:03.95,Main,,0,0,0,,What nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:06.58,Main,,0,0,0,,No matter what amazing invention you invent,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.58,0:10:10.00,Main,,0,0,0,,if you don't use it...\Nif you don't make use of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.00,0:10:12.09,Main,,0,0,0,,...it means nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:16.80,Main,,0,0,0,,That so-called joy of discovery\Nthat you scientists feel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.80,0:10:19.30,Main,,0,0,0,,is nothing but self-gratification.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.30,0:10:21.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Without men like me in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:24.72,Main,,0,0,0,,your discoveries and inventions mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:26.85,Main,,0,0,0,,They're treasures going to rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.85,0:10:32.40,Main,,0,0,0,,The joy of invention is nothing\Nbut crude sentimentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:33.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:36.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Invention and discoveries mean nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:39.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!\NWhat would you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.62,0:10:46.37,Main,,0,0,0,,The scientists I've met have\Ngone through so many failures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:49.67,Main,,0,0,0,,They've failed over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:53.42,Main,,0,0,0,,But they keep trying, again and again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.42,0:10:55.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is interesting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:10:59.80,Main,,0,0,0,,The more you think,\Nthe more you investigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:02.34,Main,,0,0,0,,the closer you come to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.34,0:11:06.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Well done is better than well said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.18,0:11:10.19,Main,,0,0,0,,The future... it's like a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:13.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.27,0:11:17.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari... Thanks to you, I feel like I've been\Nable to see something I couldn't see before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:19.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:22.61,Main,,0,0,0,,There are many interesting\Nthings in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:24.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:28.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Electromagnetic waves...\NMy research did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:33.75,Main,,0,0,0,,But even if I fail 1,000 times,\NI'll keep going until I succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.75,0:11:38.09,Main,,0,0,0,,They all believed in science,\Nand their own dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.68,0:11:44.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:45.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:53.40,Main,,0,0,0,,We create what we imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:55.94,Main,,0,0,0,,That's what's so great about science!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:58.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Someone discovers something,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:12:00.65,Main,,0,0,0,,someone else picks up on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:04.66,Main,,0,0,0,,and it expands into more and\Nmore discoveries and inventions!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.66,0:12:08.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Someone like you, who just uses\Nthings other people made...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:10.75,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't let you insult them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.29,0:12:17.38,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:18.38,Main,,0,0,0,,We can get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.38,0:12:20.26,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:40.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's how it ends?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:53.54,Main,,0,0,0,,For a man who wanted to make\Nmoney off the matter transporter
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:12:57.88,Main,,0,0,0,,to be tripped by an invention\Nused for making money...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.43,0:13:12.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:14.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.43,0:13:15.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:16.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.48,0:13:17.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Akira! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.90,0:13:21.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage... Where's Mr. Mikage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.69,0:13:23.15,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:26.57,Main,,0,0,0,,It won't hold out any longer.\NGet to safety, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:29.57,Main,,0,0,0,,No! Return Mr. Mikage right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:31.12,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:33.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Give it up. It's too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:35.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, you two, come along!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:36.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.04,0:13:39.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage... Mr. Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:40.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:42.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:45.55,Main,,0,0,0,,A fire?! What about\NMr. Mikage and Ms. Kuroki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.55,0:13:47.05,Main,,0,0,0,,They're still in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.05,0:13:50.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Along with the doctor's wife\Nand his daughter's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:53.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:55.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:58.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Mizuki! Mizuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:00.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:01.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:04.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase! Where's Mizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.45,0:14:11.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh no... She was right behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:12.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.66,0:14:13.54,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:15.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa... Waka's still down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:16.66,Main,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:18.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.33,0:14:22.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Mizuki! Where are you, Mizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:26.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Mizuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Mizuki, hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:33.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:36.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Hey, Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.60,0:14:37.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.32,0:14:46.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:47.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.26,0:15:10.68,Main,,0,0,0,,So Sekota was working with Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.68,0:15:13.35,Main,,0,0,0,,It all burned down, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:17.93,Main,,0,0,0,,This is for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:19.68,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.68,0:15:21.02,Main,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.02,0:15:26.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:31.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling better?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.53,0:15:32.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:35.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I got some rest in the back\Nof the ambulance. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.49,0:15:38.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad! I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.62,0:15:42.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I went back for the book,\Nand I breathed in some smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.37,0:15:46.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Sheesh! What would you\Nhave done without me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:53.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Y-Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.34,0:15:55.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:57.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa, you're all red.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:00.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm glad we're all safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:02.06,Main,,0,0,0,,We are not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.06,0:16:08.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:09.44,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:12.99,Main,,0,0,0,,This was all your fault from the beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:15.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Three years without a single call...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:20.12,Main,,0,0,0,,And you stole a cup from Napoleon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.12,0:16:20.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.95,0:16:24.08,Main,,0,0,0,,That wasn't stolen. It was a gift--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:28.00,Main,,0,0,0,,You are always so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:32.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:38.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.85,0:16:40.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:43.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:46.31,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.31,0:16:48.02,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:52.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey... You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:16:56.91,Main,,0,0,0,,It... It shouldn't have been this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:58.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I-I failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:03.00,Main,,0,0,0,,How could I have failed like...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.00,0:17:04.50,Main,,0,0,0,,What a failure...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.71,0:17:08.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Failure is an ingredient\Nfor success, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.17,0:17:13.67,Main,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.67,0:17:19.68,Main,,0,0,0,,I need to explain to the investors how\Nthe incandescent light project is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.68,0:17:25.60,Main,,0,0,0,,And they are getting a bit edgy after\Nwaiting for more than a year with no results.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:29.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Remember, I built this\Ncompany on your advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.94,0:17:31.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Opportunity...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:32.65,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:36.36,Main,,0,0,0,,It is when things go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:39.28,Main,,0,0,0,,that there is a chance for opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:42.62,Main,,0,0,0,,You have a good point there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.87,0:17:49.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:50.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Teacher, bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:52.30,Main,,0,0,0,,See you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:05.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.64,0:18:08.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Really, you're just too irresponsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.27,0:18:09.56,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:11.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:18.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama! Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:20.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:25.12,Main,,0,0,0,,My, you've gotten big!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:29.33,Main,,0,0,0,,You all came to pick me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:31.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we all came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:33.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:41.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, Papa. What was that book, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.05,0:18:43.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:45.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was a magical book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:47.39,Main,,0,0,0,,From the far-distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:51.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Magical? Try to be a little more realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:57.78,Main,,0,0,0,,All science and invention is like\Nfantasy to the people of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:05.20,Main,,0,0,0,,The scientists tried to give form to things\Nthat existed solely in their imaginations,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.20,0:19:08.50,Main,,0,0,0,,with unwavering hard work and passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:20.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Some day, someone will discover\Nthe principle behind TSS
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:22.14,Main,,0,0,0,,and put it into practical use.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:24.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:27.06,Main,,0,0,0,,You read the entire book, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:28.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:29.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:35.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Then you know what will happen\Nwhen it is put into practical use, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:38.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Even so, I will do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:43.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if it seems like that will\Nput things in the wrong direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.07,0:19:44.57,Main,,0,0,0,,...Mari will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.83,0:19:49.33,Main,,0,0,0,,You can have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:51.87,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't need it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:03.38,Main,,0,0,0,,In 1910, when Edison\Ninvented the toaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.38,0:20:07.43,Main,,0,0,0,,he used the press to publish the idea,\N"Two meals a day is unhealthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:10.35,Main,,0,0,0,,We should all eat three meals a day."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.35,0:20:14.15,Main,,0,0,0,,From this, the practice of three\Nmeals a day quickly spread,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:16.44,Main,,0,0,0,,and became entrenched.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:19.98,Main,,0,0,0,,And at the same time,\Nsales of the toaster rapidly spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:22.07,Main,,0,0,0,,He wasn't just an inventor,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:24.49,Main,,0,0,0,,he was also an\Nexcellent businessman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:32.00,Main,,0,0,0,,He was also an\Nexcellent businessman, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:37.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gilbert, Mr. Franklin,\NMr. Volta, Mr. Faraday,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:42.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Morse, Mr. Bell,\NMr. Hertz, Mr. Edison...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.38,0:20:44.63,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to work hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:49.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Believing that someday,\NI can create what I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.15,0:21:00.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! The needle's spinning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:05.15,Main,,0,0,0,,This was the principle on\Nwhich the motor was based.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:07.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't science interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:08.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:13.66,Main,,0,0,0,,When I grow up, I'm going to be\Na scientist like you, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.62,0:21:18.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:20.13,Main,,0,0,0,,...this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.13,0:21:24.34,Main,,0,0,0,,What? But isn't that\Nyour treasure, Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:26.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.22,0:21:28.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.05,0:21:29.93,Main,,0,0,0,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.93,0:21:33.39,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a good luck charm for those\Nwho wish to become scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.39,0:21:34.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.56,0:21:36.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.52,0:21:38.73,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.73,0:21:40.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.32,0:21:43.48,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't find a book.\NIt was supposed to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.48,0:21:44.74,Main,,0,0,0,,A book?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.74,0:21:46.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.07,0:21:50.28,Main,,0,0,0,,It was about the history of inventions\Nthat involve electricity and magnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:53.91,Main,,0,0,0,,In its place, I found this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.96,0:21:57.33,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.33,0:21:59.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Someone might be playing a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.71,0:22:01.17,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll investigate right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.17,0:22:03.13,Main,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:08.55,Main,,0,0,0,,That book has flown\Naway to guide someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.55,0:22:12.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Flown away to guide someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.22,0:22:14.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.27,0:22:20.65,Main,,0,0,0,,To a girl... in the age of creating\Nwhat you imagine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:00.75,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.75,0:24:03.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.12,0:24:04.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.17,0:24:07.25,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the toaster that Edison invented!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.25,0:24:09.80,Main,,0,0,0,,It looks so fancy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.34,0:24:13.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.13,0:24:15.43,Main,,0,0,0,,It flipped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.43,0:24:16.18,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:20.06,Main,,0,0,0,,It was simple, but it was made\Nto bake both sides properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.06,0:24:21.31,Main,,0,0,0,,How convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.31,0:24:25.69,Main,,0,0,0,,And here's a percolator for making\Ncoffee in a matching design.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.69,0:24:29.11,Main,,0,0,0,,It was sold with cups and sugar tins, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.11,0:24:31.32,Main,,0,0,0,,He made it part of a series!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.32,0:24:33.91,Main,,0,0,0,,And fans, and heaters...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.91,0:24:35.53,Main,,0,0,0,,...irons, curling irons...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.53,0:24:39.83,Main,,0,0,0,,...sewing machines... he continually\Ncreated new household electronics
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.83,0:24:43.58,Main,,0,0,0,,to bring us an era of luxurious\Nlives through electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.58,0:24:45.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.04,0:24:48.00,Main,,0,0,0,,He really had it all coordinated!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.00,0:24:50.55,Main,,0,0,0,,All I knew about Edison's\Ninventions were the light bulb,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.55,0:24:53.84,Main,,0,0,0,,the phonograph, the copier,\Nand a few other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.84,0:24:56.59,Main,,0,0,0,,But he really invented so much, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.59,0:25:00.39,Main,,0,0,0,,What was amazing about him is that,\Nfor instance, when inventing the light bulb,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.39,0:25:04.02,Main,,0,0,0,,he also invented the socket,\Nthe outlet, and the plug.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.02,0:25:07.40,Main,,0,0,0,,He always created\Nsupplements to his inventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.40,0:25:11.53,Main,,0,0,0,,And many of those remain the same today.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.53,0:25:15.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Then this socket is Mr. Edison's invention?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.24,0:25:17.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.45,0:25:20.87,Main,,0,0,0,,He made all kinds of things\Nhe imagined practical!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.87,0:25:21.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N"Create what you imagine!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.74,0:25:24.58,Main,,0,0,0,,He really did create what he imagined!\N"Create what you imagine!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.58,0:25:27.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'm gonna imagine things, too!\N"Create what you imagine!"
